# src/infrastructure/

The **infrastructure layer** — concrete implementations of the contracts
declared in `../domain/`, plus everything that talks to the outside world.

Belongs here:
- Repository implementations (SQL, ORM, key-value store, in-memory for tests)
- HTTP / gRPC / message-queue clients
- File and network I/O
- Email / SMS / push-notification adapters
- Caching backends
- Time, UUID, and other "impure" providers behind a domain-level interface

Does **not** belong here:
- Business rules
- Use-case orchestration
- Any module that other layers may import directly without going through a
  domain-layer interface

The rule of thumb: `../domain/` declares **what** is needed; this layer
provides **how** it's done. Wiring (which concrete implementation gets
injected where) happens at the composition root, not here.

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/architecture.md`.
